DOC.brief_summary: The primary overall objective of this study is to characterize the levels of and compare levels of the ADRB3 receptor in human non-pregnant myometrium, pregnant myometrium at different time points in pregnancy, in normal and dysfunctional labor and also to measure levels and expression of these receptors in placental arteries at different maturation statuses of placenta and in pre-eclampsia/hypertension
DOC.criteria: Women undergoing cesarian section Interkurrent diseases
